claim.claim-text:
6. A web processing system having at least a winding device for winding a web, said winding device comprising: 
a drive shaft having a ring; 
an annular conductor pressed against and secured to an outer circumferential surface of said ring; and 
a holder rotatably mounted on said drive shaft in covering relation to said ring, for winding the web therearound; 
said holder supporting on an inner circumferential surface thereof a magnet row of a plurality of magnets; 
said magnet row facing said annular conductor.

13. A web processing system having at least a winding device for winding a web, said winding device comprising: 
a drive shaft having a torque transmitter; 
a support fixed to said torque transmitter; 
an annular conductor pressed against and secured to an outer circumferential surface of said support; and 
a holder rotatably mounted on said drive shaft in covering relation to said support, for winding the web therearound; 
said holder supporting on an inner circumferential surface thereof a magnet row of a plurality of magnets (208) with a magnet holder; 
said magnet row facing said annular conductor.

20. A web processing system having at least a web slitting device for slitting a wider web into a plurality of narrower webs, said web slitting device comprising: 
a rotary blade assembly for slitting a wider web which is being fed, along the direction of feed into a plurality of narrower webs; and 
side edge delivery means for delivering side edges produced from said wider web when the wider web is slit into said narrower webs; 
said side edge delivery means comprising: 
a side edge delivery roller rotatable in a direction to deliver the side edges; 
a nip roller rotatable with said side edge delivery roller while gripping the side edges between said side edge delivery roller and said nip roller; and 
a nip roller pressing mechanism for pressing said nip roller against said side edge delivery roller under a predetermined pressure; 
said side edge delivery roller being rotatable at a peripheral speed higher than a peripheral speed of said rotary blade assembly.
